# Known Behaviors

## Button/Container: Width="auto" gives wrong size (by design)

Container is a positioning widget, not a layout widget. When Width="auto", Container.GetRaw()
returns an empty array (width=0) because it has no intrinsic size calculation. The Renderer's
StackPanel layout then falls back to MeasureChildrenMainAxis which may produce an incorrect
size (too small or too large depending on context).

This is intentional and a consequence of backwards compatibility: Container was designed for
absolute positioning with explicit sizes. StackPanel was later added as the layout widget with
proper auto-sizing. The XmlParser compensates for Buttons specifically by pre-calculating
width from text content when the Width attribute is omitted entirely.

Rule: never set Width="auto" on Button/Container. Either omit Width (XmlParser calculates)
or use an explicit value ("10ch", "100%", "fill").
